üèéÔ∏è Constructors
A constructor is the company or team that designs and builds the chassis (and sometimes the engine) of the F1 car. Examples:
Mercedes-AMG Petronas
Scuderia Ferrari
Red Bull Racing
----------------------
Each constructor is responsible for:
Designing the car
Registering for the championship
Competing with two drivers under their team
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üìä ConstructorStandings
This refers to the Championship points table for constructors. Teams earn points based on their drivers' race finishes.
-------------------------------------------------
Points from both drivers are added for the team total.
The Constructor's Championship is separate from the Driver's Championship.
It determines team rankings and prize money at season‚Äôs end.
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üèÅ ConstructorResults
These are race-by-race results for a constructor across the season. It includes:
-------------------------------------------------
Finishing positions of each driver
Points scored in that race
DNFs (Did Not Finish), penalties, etc.
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üìç Circuits
Each circuit is a unique race track or venue. Examples:
-------------------------------------------------
Monza (Italy)
Silverstone (UK)
Suzuka (Japan)
Details include:
Track length
Number of laps
Layout
Location and weather characteristics
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üõë PitStops
These are when a car stops in the pit lane during a race or qualifying session.
-------------------------------------------------
Common reasons:
Tyre change (most frequent)
Front wing repair
Serving penalties (like 5-second or 10-second stop-go)
Pit stop data includes:
Driver
Time of stop (lap number)
Duration
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
‚ö° SprintResults
These are the results of a Sprint Race, a shorter race (usually ~100 km) held on certain weekends.
-------------------------------------------------
Key points:
Usually on Saturday before the main race
Offers points (though fewer than a full race)
Sets the grid for the main race (in some formats)
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üèÜ Results
Refers to final classifications of a race:
-------------------------------------------------
Positions of all drivers
Lap times
Points awarded
Gaps to the winner or next car
Often used for both qualifying results and race results.
-------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------
üèéÔ∏è constructors
Describes the F1 constructor teams.
================================================================
| Column           | Description                               |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `constructorId`  | Primary key (internal ID for team)        |
| `constructorRef` | Unique string reference (e.g., `ferrari`) |
| `name`           | Full team name (e.g., `Scuderia Ferrari`) |
| `nationality`    | Team nationality (e.g., `Italian`)        |
| `url`            | Link to official constructor profile      |
================================================================
üìä constructorStandings
Points table for constructors per race.
=======================================================================
| Column                   | Description                             |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| `constructorStandingsId` | Primary key                             |
| `raceId`                 | Foreign key to `races` table            |
| `constructorId`          | Foreign key to `constructors` table     |
| `points`                 | Points scored in that race              |
| `position`               | Position in standings (as of that race) |
| `positionText`           | Text version (e.g., `R` for retired)    |
| `wins`                   | Number of wins so far in the season     |
=======================================================================
üèÅ constructorResults
Individual race results for each constructor. (Not always populated in Ergast)
===============================================================
| Column                 | Description                        |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `constructorResultsId` | Primary key                        |
| `raceId`               | Foreign key to `races`             |
| `constructorId`        | Foreign key to `constructors`      |
| `points`               | Points scored in that race by team |
| `status`               | Status (optional or legacy)        |
===============================================================
üìç circuits
Information about each race circuit.
=======================================================
| Column       | Description                          |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| `circuitId`  | Primary key                          |
| `circuitRef` | Unique string (e.g., `silverstone`)  |
| `name`       | Official circuit name                |
| `location`   | City or locality                     |
| `country`    | Country                              |
| `lat`, `lng` | Latitude and longitude (for mapping) |
| `alt`        | Altitude (optional)                  |
| `url`        | URL to more info                     |
=======================================================
üõë pitStops
Pit stop data per driver per race.
==========================================================
| Column     | Description                               |
| ---------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `raceId`   | Foreign key to `races`                    |
| `driverId` | Foreign key to `drivers`                  |
| `stop`     | Pit stop number (1, 2, ...)               |
| `lap`      | Lap during which the stop occurred        |
| `time`     | Timestamp or race time when stop occurred |
| `duration` | Length of stop (e.g., `2.5` seconds)      |
==========================================================
‚ö° sprintResults
Results of Sprint races. Only present for seasons since 2021.
=================================================================
| Column          | Description                                 |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `raceId`        | Foreign key to `races`                      |
| `driverId`      | Foreign key to `drivers`                    |
| `constructorId` | Foreign key to `constructors`               |
| `number`        | Car number                                  |
| `grid`          | Starting position in the sprint             |
| `position`      | Final position in the sprint                |
| `positionText`  | Final result (can include letters like DNF) |
| `points`        | Points awarded for the sprint               |
| `laps`          | Number of laps completed                    |
| `statusId`      | Foreign key to `status`                     |
=================================================================
üèÜ results
Main race results per driver per race.
=====================================================================
| Column            | Description                                   |
| ----------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `resultId`        | Primary key                                   |
| `raceId`          | Foreign key to `races`                        |
| `driverId`        | Foreign key to `drivers`                      |
| `constructorId`   | Foreign key to `constructors`                 |
| `grid`            | Starting grid position                        |
| `position`        | Final finishing position                      |
| `positionText`    | Text version (DNF, DQ, NC, etc.)              |
| `points`          | Points earned                                 |
| `laps`            | Laps completed                                |
| `time`            | Total race time (nullable if DNF)             |
| `milliseconds`    | Race time in milliseconds                     |
| `fastestLap`      | Lap number of fastest lap (if any)            |
| `rank`            | Rank of fastest lap time (across drivers)     |
| `fastestLapTime`  | Time string (e.g., `1:31.478`)                |
| `fastestLapSpeed` | Speed (in km/h)                               |
| `statusId`        | Foreign key to `status` (reason if DNF, etc.) |
=====================================================================
üèáraces
========================================================
| Column      | Description                            |
| ----------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `raceId`    | Primary key                            |
| `year`      | Season year                            |
| `round`     | Race number in the season              |
| `circuitId` | Foreign key to `circuits`              |
| `name`      | Race name (e.g., `British Grand Prix`) |
| `date`      | Race date                              |
| `time`      | Start time                             |
| `url`       | Official race URL                      |
========================================================
üöó drivers
| Column                | Description                 |
| --------------------- | --------------------------- |
| `driverId`            | Primary key                 |
| `driverRef`           | Unique string               |
| `code`                | 3-letter code (e.g., `HAM`) |
| `forename`, `surname` | Driver's full name          |
| `dob`                 | Date of birth               |
| `nationality`         | Driver's nationality        |
| `url`                 | Official profile link       |
========================================================
status                                                        
| ---------- |--------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `statusId` | Primary key                                            |
| `status`   | Reason for finishing or not (e.g., `Finished`, `Collision`,`Engine`)  | 
